-- Sautero — adds ~730 new ingredients to the price book, bringing the total from 533 to
-- roughly 1,263. This is the demo/presentation-scoped ~1300-ingredient set, NOT the full
-- 20,000-row "master ingredient database" concept discussed elsewhere and separately paused —
-- that multi-table spec does not apply here.
--
-- Same honesty standard as 06_ingredients_seed.sql, 14_nutrition_seed.sql and
-- 31_ingredients_backfill_storage_season.sql: every price, nutrition value, storage_type and
-- season below is a reasoned estimate from general professional-kitchen, culinary and
-- food-science knowledge (USDA/Swiss Food Composition-style references for nutrition), NOT
-- individually verified against a real supplier quote or lab analysis. Treat every value as a
-- strong starting point to check and correct from real experience, not a confirmed fact.
-- price_currency is kept as 'EUR' to stay consistent with the existing 533 rows in
-- 06_ingredients_seed.sql (no strong reason to introduce a second currency into one price
-- book — Richard can re-price into CHF from the app's Ingredients & Pricing screen if he
-- prefers). notes/substitutes/origin are left NULL where nothing genuinely useful was known,
-- rather than padded with filler text. seasons is an empty array for anything year-round or
-- non-seasonal by nature (most spices, dry goods, alcohol, sauces, cured meat, cheese) —
-- only genuinely seasonal fresh produce, fish and a few pastry ingredients (chestnuts,
-- truffles) carry a real season.
--
-- New coverage, prioritized per Richard's brief (sushi/Japanese-trained chef in a Swiss hotel
-- kitchen): a standalone Seafood category with species-level fish/shellfish/roe; deeper
-- Japanese/Asian pantry (miso types, rice vinegar/sake/mirin grades, kombu grades, real vs.
-- horseradish-based wasabi, togarashi, ponzu, Korean/Chinese/Southeast Asian ferments and
-- sauces); nuts, seeds, legumes and pulses; alcohol actually used in cooking (not a
-- sommelier wine list); more Swiss/European AOP/AOC/DOP cheeses; condiments, sauces and
-- ferments; baking/pâtisserie specifics (couverture percentages, specialty flours, gelling
-- agents, Swiss baking staples); and species-level vegetables, fruit, herbs, spices, meat
-- cuts/charcuterie, poultry/game birds and grains rounding out what a 25-station hotel
-- kitchen actually stocks.
--
-- Run AFTER 06_ingredients_seed.sql and 31_ingredients_backfill_storage_season.sql. Every name
-- here was checked against the existing 533-row set (case-insensitive) to avoid collisions with
-- the unique (kitchen_id, lower(name)) index on the ingredients table. Safe to run once; running
-- twice will violate that unique index rather than silently duplicate rows.


